[SN]TITLE[SN]
Four arrested after riot police called to Glasgow flat

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four people have been arrested after a man allegedly barricaded himself inside a flat in Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Riot police and dogs were among emergency services called to the property in Ibrox Street in the Cessnock area at about 18:10 on Friday.
At one point more than 10 police cars, five ambulances, riot police, dogs, and fire engines were at the scene.
A police spokeswoman said three men and a woman were arrested at 23:50. They were put in police custody.
